    "notes": "Regional atlas — five racial homelands radiate from the central metropolis Caelum-by-the-Wash, with two small towns lining each spoke. The races invert the genre defaults: humans are brittle specialists; elves are conniving merchants; dwarves are tall sky-dwelling orchardists; halflings are naval mercenaries; orcs are quiet philosophers. The atlas is consumed by the narrator (when surfacing regional flavor), the picker (when offering form/region pairs), and any UI that wants to render the world map. The graph is acyclic from each spoke's perspective — towns appear in order of distance from Caelum."
  },

